<p class="title">Sawn Off 12 Gauge
Double-Barrelled Shotgun (Handcannon)</p>

<p style="text-align:center;"><img src="https://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.actiongames.co.uk/tnn/guide/hc.jpg" border="0"></p>

<table align="center" class="standard" cellpadding="2">
<tr>
<td colspan="2" bgcolor="green">Statistics</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td bgcolor="#999999">Caliber</td>
<td bgcolor="#999999">12 Gauge</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td bgcolor="#CCCCCC">Magazine Capacity</td>
<td bgcolor="#CCCCCC">2 Shells (1 per barrel)</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td bgcolor="#999999">Overall Length</td>
<td bgcolor="#999999">203.2 mm</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td bgcolor="#CCCCCC">Width</td>
<td bgcolor="#CCCCCC">101.6 mm</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td bgcolor="#999999">Height</td>
<td bgcolor="#999999">101.6 mm</td>
</tr>

</table>

<p class="title">Details</p>

<p>You only get one shot from this gun before you have
to reload since it fires both of it's shells out at once, the
reload time is extremely long, and the weapon is completely useless
at anything more than close range. So why use the handcannon at
all? Because if you hit somebody at close range they'll either die
from the blast or die from the impact with that wall on the other
side of the map.<br>
It's a tricky gun to master and you have to get very close to the
enemy to use it but once you get the hang of it you'll be dealing
out more damage than any other weapon in the game.<br>
Best used in confined spaces such as corridors.</p>

